1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,142
When you think about helping young people

2
00:00:03,192 --> 00:00:06,335
stay motivated at work,

3
00:00:06,385 --> 00:00:09,527
you have to start with what they actually care about.

4
00:00:09,577 --> 00:00:12,719
It is not just a paycheck.

5
00:00:12,769 --> 00:00:15,911
They want to feel like the work matters,

6
00:00:15,961 --> 00:00:19,104
and that someone notices the effort.

7
00:00:19,154 --> 00:00:22,296
Give them context for the bigger picture

8
00:00:22,346 --> 00:00:25,488
so the small daily tasks feel connected.

9
00:00:25,538 --> 00:00:28,680
Real feedback, in the moment,

10
00:00:28,730 --> 00:00:31,873
is one of the most powerful tools we have.

11
00:00:31,923 --> 00:00:35,065
Don't wait for an annual review

12
00:00:35,115 --> 00:00:38,257
to tell them where they stand.

13
00:00:38,307 --> 00:00:41,450
Show them a path that goes somewhere.

14
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:44,642
If they cannot see growth, they leave.

15
00:00:44,692 --> 00:00:47,834
Build trust by listening to what's hard,

16
00:00:47,884 --> 00:00:51,026
and acting on what you hear.

17
00:00:51,076 --> 00:00:54,219
Pair them with people who invest in them.

18
00:00:54,269 --> 00:00:57,411
A good mentor changes everything early on.

19
00:00:57,461 --> 00:01:00,603
Celebrate the wins, even the small ones,

20
00:01:00,653 --> 00:01:03,795
because momentum is what keeps people going.

21
00:01:03,845 --> 00:01:06,988
When you do these things consistently,

22
00:01:07,038 --> 00:01:10,180
young people don't just stay — they thrive.

